# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#Method int computeRegionComplexity() const
#In incomplete
#Line # incomplete ##

Returns a value that grows approximately linearly with the number of
intervals comprised in the region. Empty region will return zero, Rect
will return 1, complex will return a value greater than one.
Use this to compare two regions, where the larger count likely
indicates a more complex region.

#Return incomplete ##

#Example
// incomplete
##

#SeeAlso incomplete

